//! Unicode 17.0 property-escape expansions for the properties whose
//! Test262 `built-ins/RegExp/property-escapes/generated` cases fail against a
//! `regex-syntax` 0.8.x that bundles the Unicode 16.0 UCD. The four brand-new
//! Unicode-17 *scripts* live in `unicode17.rs`; this file carries the U17 data
//! for pre-existing properties that gained (or, rarely, lost) code points.
//!
//! Every range set is derived offline by diffing each generated test's own
//! embedded UCD-17 `matchSymbols` against the UCD-16 table the crate ships:
//!   * `Delta` — the crate is correct at UCD 16 and UCD 17 only *adds* points;
//!     the added ranges are unioned into the crate class (`[\p{Prop}<delta>]`).
//!   * `Full` — the crate cannot represent the property (`Script=Unknown`,
//!     `Changes_When_NFKC_Casefolded`) or UCD 17 *removed* points from it (so a
//!     union would over-match); the complete UCD-17 range set replaces it.
//!
//! This file is generated data — see the PR body for the regeneration recipe.

/// How a matched U17 property expands.
pub(super) enum U17Expansion {
    /// Ranges to union into the crate's own `\p{Prop}` class.
    Delta(&'static str),
    /// Complete replacement range set; the crate class is bypassed.
    Full(&'static str),
}

